    • Field Detail

      • boxFillColor

        @Option
public String boxFillColor
        CSS fill color used for the box.

      • boxLineColor

        @Option
public String boxLineColor
        CSS line color used to outline the box.

      • maxValue

        @Option
public Double maxValue
        If minvalue and maxvalue are set then the scale of the plot is fixed. By default minValue and maxValue are deduced from the values supplied.

      • medianColor

        @Option
public String medianColor
        CSS color used to draw the median line.

      • minValue

        @Option
public Double minValue
        If minvalue and maxvalue are set then the scale of the plot is fixed. By default minValue and maxValue are deduced from the values supplied.

      • outlierIQR

        @Option
public Double outlierIQR
        Set the inter-quartile range multiplier used to calculate values that qualify as an outlier.

        Default: 1.5

      • outlierLineColor

        @Option
public String outlierLineColor
        CSS color used to draw the outlier circles.

      • raw

        @Option
public Boolean raw
        If set to false, then the values supplied are used to calculate the box data points for you. If true then you must pre-calculate the points (see below).

        Default: false

      • showOutliers

        @Option
public Boolean showOutliers
        If true, then outliers (values > 1.5x the IQR) are marked with circles and the whiskers are placed at Q1 and Q3 instead of the least and greatest value.

        Default: true

      • spotRadius

        @Option
public String spotRadius
        Radius in pixels to draw the outlier circles.

      • target

        @Option
public Double target
        If set to a value, then a small crosshair is drawn at that point to represent a target value.

      • targetColor

        @Option
public String targetColor
        CSS color used to draw the target crosshair.

      • whiskerColor

        @Option
public String whiskerColor
        CSS color used to draw the whiskers.

      • tooltipFormatFieldlist

        @Option
public String[] tooltipFormatFieldlist
        An array of values specifying which fields to display in a tooltip and in what order.

      • tooltipFormatFieldlistKey

        @Option
public String tooltipFormatFieldlistKey
        Specifies which key holds the field name to reference above. For box plots this should be "field".
